title: [Gyldemar Green, Forest]
description: Looking around, you can see trees in all stages of growth and decay.  This forest has reached an equilibrium that includes constant change within it.  A small dark speck flits into a young tanik ahead, and then disappears.  It is a wren, which has an impressive call for such a small bird.
